subject:

MAKING THE RIGHT CHOICE (read Mk. 8:34-38)
===================================================================
verse:

What good is it for a man to gain the whole world, yet
forfeit his soul? (Mk. 8:36)

===================================================================
reflection:

Let us remember that when we acknowledge Christ as Lord and
Savior, He enriches us with the greatest treasure---
salvation. Which He earned for us by His death as the
sacrificial Lamb of God. In the light of Christ's love for
us, and by the strength of faith that the Holy Spirit gives
in Baptism and sustains in Communion, we can make the right
choices. Let us have the mind of Joshua who said in chapter
24:15, "As for me and my household, we will serve the Lord."
Let us always ask, [How can I best serve the Lord?]

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord Jesus, thank You for the gift of salvation earned by
Your sacrifice as the Lamb of God. Strengthen our faith
through Baptism and Communion, that we may always choose to
serve You with the mind of Joshua. Help us to faithfully
ask, "How can I best serve the Lord?" and to live our lives
in joyful obedience to Your will. Amen. (AI)

